<section id="overview">
<title>Course roadmap</title>
    <para id="tour">
The novel research-oriented course of bioinformatics called <cite><cite-title>From Sequence to Expression and Structure</cite-title></cite> is organized into three main parts listed below.
<list id="content" list-type="enumerated">
  <title>Course structure</title>
  <item>Statistical methods for gene expression and gene interaction using DNA-array data as well as other genomic data</item>
  <item>Statistical machine learning techniques for bioinformatics</item>
  <item>Application of computational geometry and robotics techniques to the study of biomolecules and receptor-ligand interactions</item>
</list>
  </para>

